my|date=2016-02-20|last2=Healy|first2=Patrick|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-10-21}}</ref>\n\nClinton had campaigned heavily in the state, airing an ad in which she comforted a young [[Latin Americans|Latinx]] girl who was worried her parents would be [[Deportation|deported]]. Clinton's message appeared to resonate with [[Hispanic]] and [[African Americans|African American]] voters, with Clinton winning by large margins in many diverse neighborhoods in populous [[Clark County, Nevada|Clark County]], especially in caucuses in [[Las Vegas]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{2016 Democratic primaries}}\n\n[[Category:2016 United States Democratic presidential primaries by state|Nevada]]\n[[Category:Nevada Democratic caucuses|2016]]\n[[Category:2016 Nevada elections|Democratic caucuses]]\n[[Category:Political conventions in Nevada|Democratic, 2016]]\n", "name_user": "Cpcallen", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Undid revision 945576669 byEdificio Barro(talk))", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_Nevada_Democratic_caucuses_and_convention"}
