]]\n| align=center|0<!--Saenuri-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |-  \n| align=center|3 <!--DUP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n| align=center|0<!--UPP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n| align=center|0 <!--LFP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=center |- \n| align=center|0 <!--CKP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n| align=center|0 <!--Independent-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- \n| align=center|3\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n|-\n| [[Sejong City|Sejong]]\n| align=center|0<!--Saenuri-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=center |-  \n| align=center|1 <!--DUP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=center|+ 1\n| align=center|0<!--UPP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=center|-\n| align=center|0 <!--LFP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- \n| align=center|0 <!--CKP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n| align=center|0 <!--Independent-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- \n| align=center|1\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=center|+ 1\n|-\n| Proportional<br />representation\n| align=center|25 <!--Saenuri-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 5  \n| align=center|21 <!--DUP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|+ 6\n| align=center|6<!--UPP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|+ 3\n| align=center|2 <!--LFP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 2 \n| align=center|0 <!--CKP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|- 2\n| align=center|0 <!--Independent-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- \n| align=center|54\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|-\n|-\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\" align=left|Total\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|152 <!--Saenuri-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 15  \n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|127 <!--DUP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|+ 46\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|13<!--UPP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|+ 8\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|5 <!--LFP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 13 \n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|0 <!--CKP-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 3 \n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|3 <!--Independent-->\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center |- 22 \n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|300\n!style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"  align=center|+ 1\n|}\n\n==Reactions and aftermath==\nPresident Lee said that the \"people made wise choices. The government will do its best to manage state affairs in a stable manner and take care of the people's livelihood\". The DUP's secretary-general Park Sun-sook conceded the election and added: \"The DUP failed to turn public calls for punishing the ... ruling party into reality. We apologise for disappointing supporters. We will sincerely think over what today's election means and try ceaselessly to be reborn as a party the people can lean and rely on.\"<ref name=\"aljazresult\" /> Sim Dae-pyung, leader of the Liberty Forward Party, announced his resignation after the party's poor performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/national/2012/04/12/33/0301000000AEN20120412004100315F.HTML|title=Ruling party leader pledges new beginning after election win|work=YONHAP NEWS|date=12 April 2012|accessdate=15 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April, the DUP leader Han Myeong-sook announced her resignation on account of her party's defeat.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2012/04/117_108895.html|title=Opposition leader steps down over election defeat|date=13 April 2012|accessdate=13 April 2012|work=The Korea Times}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n:1.{{note|nb1}} Comparison includes the Pro-Park Coalition, which split from and subsequently reintegrated with the Grand National Party.\n:2.{{note|nb2}} This survey asked separate questions on party support and voting intention. The latter result is reported here.\n:3.{{note|nb3}} This survey dealt specifically with seats allocated by proportional representation.\n\n==External links==\n*[http://hw.libsyn.com/p/c/c/8/cc87624469bd7658/2012_04_12_Legislative_Elections.mp3?sid=cb47038634c7b730166cedc8ae8ef17b&l_sid=26202&l_eid=&l_mid=2972714&expiration=1337402273&hwt=6c80884339d3c6edfafdee75ea60d455  Korea Society Podcast: Korea\u2019s Legislative Elections: The Day After]{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, 12 April 2012\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{South Korean elections}}\n{{National Assembly (South Korea)|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:Legislative elections in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2012 elections in Asia]]\n[[Category:2012 in South Korea]]\n", "name_user": "LC Editing", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eResults", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_South_Korean_legislative_election"}
{"title_page": "List of biology awards", "text_new": "[[File:Bronwyn Gillanders presenting gender equity forum at 2016 ASFB-OCS conference.jpg|thumb| Bronwyn Gillanders (right), former [[Australian Society for Fish Biology]] President and 2016 [[K. Radway Allen Award]] winner.]]\nThis '''list of biology awards''' is an index to articles about notable awards for [[biology]], the [[natural science]] that studies [[life]] and living [[organism]]s, including their [[anatomy|physical structure]], [[Biochemistry|chemical processes]], [[Molecular biology|molecular interactions]], [[Physiology|physiological mechanisms]], [[Developmental biology|development]] and [[evolution]]. \nIt includes a general list and lists of ecology, genetics and neuroscience awards.\nIt excludes awards for [[List of biochemistry awards|biochemistry]], [[List of biomedical science awards|biomedical science]], [[List of medicine awards|medicine]], [[List of ornithology awards|ornithology]] and [[List of paleontology awards|paleontology]], which are covered by separate lists.\n\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n==General awards==\n===International===\n\n{|Class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6em;\"| Country !!  Award !! Sponsor !!Notes\n|-\n| International || [[Alexander von Humboldt Medal (IAVS)]] || [[International Association for Vegetation Science]] || Vegetation scientist for an outstanding body of work<ref>{{citation |accessdate=2020-01-17 |url=http://iavs.org/Awards/Alexander-von-Humboldt.aspx |title=Alexander von Humboldt Medal |publisher=IAVS}}</ref>\n|-\n| International || [[Carlos J. Finlay Prize for Microbiology]] || [[UNESCO]] || Outstanding contributions to microbiology (including immunology, molecular biology, genetics, etc.) and its applications<ref>{{cite web|title = The 2003 Carlos J. Finlay Prize for Microbiology has been awarded to Professor Antonio Pe\u00f1a Diaz from Mexico|url = http://www.unesco.org/science/psd/prizes/finlay/finlay_science_prize.shtml|publisher = UNESCO}}</ref>\n|-\n|International\n|[[Edison Awards|Edison Award]]\n|[[Edison Awards]]\n|Honoring excellence in innovation\n|-\n| International || [[Harrison Prize]] || [[International Society of Developmental Biologists]] || Developmental biology<ref>[http://www.developmental-biology.org/about/about.html \"About the ISDB\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201020954/http://www.developmental-biology.org/about/about.html |date=2016-12-01 }}, International Society of Developmental Biologists.</ref>\n|-\n| International || [[Redi Award]] || [[International Society on Toxinology ]] || Significant contributions in toxinology, the scientific study of venoms, poisons and toxins<ref>{{cite journal |author= Mebs D|title= History of the International Society on Toxinology - A personal view| journal= Toxicon|year=2012| volume=69|issue= |pages= 21\u20138|pmid= 23237723|doi=10.1016/j.toxicon.2012.11.021}}</ref>\n|-\n| International || [[UNESCO-Equatorial Guinea International Prize for Research in the Life Sciences]] || [[UNESCO]] || Scientific research in the life sciences leading to improving the quality of human life<ref>[http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/science-technology/basic-sciences/life-sciences/international-prize-for-research-in-the-life-sciences/ UNESCO-Equatorial Guinea International Prize for Research in the Life Sciences on Unesco website]</ref>\n|}\n\n===Americas===\n\n{|Class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6em;\"| Country !!  Award !! Sponsor !!Notes\n|-\n| Canada || [[Flavelle Medal]] || [[Royal Society of Canada]] || Outstanding contribution to biological science<ref>{{cite web|title=Flavelle Medal|url=http://rsc.ca/en/institutional-members/medals-awards/rsc-medals-awards|work=RSC Medals & Awards|publisher=Royal Society of Canada|accessdate=21 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222080445/http://rsc.ca/en/institutional-members/medals-awards/rsc-medals-awards|archive-date=22 February 2015|url-status=dead}}</re