eb|url=http://www.faseb.org/About-FASEB/Awards/Excellence-in-Science-Award.aspx|title= FASEB Excellence in Science Award|publisher= FASEB|accessdate = 8 January 2014}} </ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Gilbert Morgan Smith Medal]] || [[National Academy of Sciences]] || Excellence in published research on marine or freshwater algae<ref> {{cite web|url= http://www.nasonline.org/programs/awards/gilbert-morgan-smith-medal.html|title= Gilbert Morgan Smith Medal|publisher= National Academy of Sciences|accessdate = 14 August 2015}} </ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[ISCB Innovator Award]] || [[International Society for Computational Biology]] || Leading scientists who are within two decades post-degree, who consistently make outstanding contributions to the field, and who continue to forge new directions<ref>{{cite web|title=ISCB Innovator Award|url=https://www.iscb.org/iscb-awards/iscb-innovator-award|website=www.iscb.org|accessdate=2 February 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Keith R. Porter Lecture]] || [[American Society for Cell Biology]] || Eminent cell biologist<ref>{{cite web| url = http://ascb.org/keith-r-porter-lecture-award/|title= Keith R. Porter Lecture Award|publisher= ASCB|accessdate = 7 January 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Kistler Prize]] || [[Foundation for the Future]] || Understanding of the connection between human heredity and human society<ref>{{citation |accessdate=2020-02-16 |url=http://www.futurefoundation.org/awards/kpr_home.htm |title=Kistler Prize |publisher=Foundation for the Future|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060811012941/http://www.futurefoundation.org/awards/kpr_home.htm |archive-date=2006-08-11 }}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Larry Sandler Memorial Award]] || [[Drosophila Research Conference]] : [[Genetics Society of America]] || Best dissertation of the preceding year<ref>[http://flybase.org/static_pages/news/DrosBoardMtgAgenda2012.pdf 2012 Drosophila Board Meeting Minutes]</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Leidy Award]] || [[Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University]] || Excellence in publications, explorations, discoveries or research in the natural sciences<ref>{{cite journal|date=June 2007|title=The Four Awards Bestowed by The Academy of Natural Sciences and Their Recipients|journal=Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia|publisher=The Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia |volume=156 |issue=1 |pages=403\u2013404 |doi=10.1635/0097-3157(2007)156[403:TFABBT]2.0.CO;2}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Louisa Gross Horwitz Prize]] || [[Columbia University]] || Outstanding contribution in basic research in the fields of biology or biochemistry<ref>[http://www.cumc.columbia.edu/research/horwitz-prize The Official Site of Louisa Gross Horwitz Prize]</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[MBC Paper of the Year]] || [[American Society for Cell Biology]] : ''[[Molecular Biology of the Cell]]'' || Paper judged to be the best of the year in the field of molecular biology<ref>{{cite journal|url = http://www.europepmc.org/articles/pmc301074/pdf/mbc00088-0002.pdf| title= Paper of the Year Award|accessdate= 11 January 2015|pmc=301074}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = O'Neill to Receive MBoC Paper of the Year Award {{!}} Anesthesiology {{!}} Washington University in St. Louis|url = http://anest.wustl.edu/about/news/oneill_to_receive_mboc_paper_of_the_year_award|website = anest.wustl.edu|accessdate = 2015-12-13}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[March of Dimes Prize in Developmental Biology]] || [[March of Dimes]] || Investigator whose research brings us closer to the day when all babies will be born healthy<ref>http://www.marchofdimes.org/news/2017-march-of-dimes-prize-awarded-to-dr-c-david-allis-for-groundbreaking-research.aspx</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Margaret Oakley Dayhoff Award]] || [[Biophysical Society]] || Woman who holds very high promise or has achieved prominence while developing the early stages of a career in biophysical research<ref>Biophysic