iology Olympiad]] || [[International Biology Olympiad]] || Competition for Iranian high school students of the age of 17-18 in the field of biology<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibo-info.org/countries/iran-1 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706062341/http://www.ibo-info.org/countries/iran-1 |archive-date=2012-07-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| Japan || [[International Prize for Biology]] || [[Japan Society for the Promotion of Science]] || Outstanding contribution to the advancement of research in fundamental biology<ref>{{citation |accessdate=2020-02-15 |url=https://www.jsps.go.jp/english/e-biol/01_outline.html |title=About the Prize |publisher=Japan Society for the Promotion of Science}}</ref>\n|-\n| Japan || [[Kihara Memorial Foundation Academic Award]] || Kihara Memorial Yokohama Foundation || Outstanding original research in life sciences<ref>[http://kihara.or.jp/english/award/science_promotion.html Kihara Memorial Foundation Academic Award]</ref><ref>{{cite web |work=\u6728\u539f\u8ca1\u56e3 |script-title=ja:\u6728\u539f\u8a18\u5ff5\u8ca1\u56e3\u5b66\u8853\u8cde\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066 |trans-title=About the Kihara Memorial Foundation Academic Award |url=http://kihara.or.jp/award/academic_award.html |accessdate=February 2, 2013 |language=Japanese |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204032857/http://kihara.or.jp/award/academic_award.html |archive-date=February 4, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| Japan || [[Kyoto Prize in Basic Sciences]] || [[Inamori Foundation]] || Global achievement in Basic Sciences<ref>{{cite web|title=Claude Elwood Shannon|url=http://www.kyotoprize.org/en/laureates/claude_elwood_shannon/|accessdate=17 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Kyoto Prize honors achievement and character|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/science/columnist/vergano/2006-11-12-kyoto-prize_x.htm|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=12 October 2014|date=11 November 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n| Pa