ward/science_promotion.html Kihara Memorial Foundation Academic Award]</ref><ref>{{cite web |work=\u6728\u539f\u8ca1\u56e3 |script-title=ja:\u6728\u539f\u8a18\u5ff5\u8ca1\u56e3\u5b66\u8853\u8cde\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066 |trans-title=About the Kihara Memorial Foundation Academic Award |url=http://kihara.or.jp/award/academic_award.html |accessdate=February 2, 2013 |language=Japanese |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204032857/http://kihara.or.jp/award/academic_award.html |archive-date=February 4, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| Japan || [[Kyoto Prize in Basic Sciences]] || [[Inamori Foundation]] || Global achievement in Basic Sciences<ref>{{cite web|title=Claude Elwood Shannon|url=http://www.kyotoprize.org/en/laureates/claude_elwood_shannon/|accessdate=17 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Kyoto Prize honors achievement and character|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/science/columnist/vergano/2006-11-12-kyoto-prize_x.htm|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=12 October 2014|date=11 November 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n| Pakistan || [[Abdus Salam Award]] || [[International Centre for Theoretical Physics]], Pakistan chapter || Young Pakistani scientists for their research in chemistry, mathematics, physics or biology<ref>{{Cite web| title =Nominations sought for Abdus Salam Prize in Biology.   | publisher =   | date =   | url = http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Nominations+sought+for+Abdus+Salam+Prize+in+Biology.-a0197013559 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title =  Nominations sought for Abdus Salam Prize| publisher =  | date =  April 27, 2010| url =  http://news.wateen.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=12829| format =  | doi =  | accessdate =  }}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n| South Korea || [[Korean Biology Olympiad]] || Korean Biology Educational Society || Finalists become eligible to join the [[International Biology Olympiad]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://kbo.bioedu.kr/|title=KBO - \ud55c\uad6d \uc0d