netics is a branch of [[biology]] concerned with the study of [[gene]]s, [[genetic variation]], and [[heredity]] in [[organism]]s.<ref name=griffiths2000sect60>{{cite book |editor-first=Anthony J.F. |editor-last=Griffiths |editor2-first=Jeffrey H. |editor2-last=Miller |editor3-first=David T. |editor3-last=Suzuki |editor4-first=Richard C. |editor4-last=Lewontin |editor5-last=Gelbart |title=An Introduction to Genetic Analysis |year=2000 |isbn=978-0-7167-3520-5 |edition=7th |publisher=W.H. Freeman |location=New York |chapterurl=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/bv.fcgi?rid=iga.section.60 |chapter=Genetics and the Organism: Introduction}}</ref><ref name=Hartl_and_Jones>Hartl D, Jones E (2005)</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/genetics|title=the definition of genetics|website=www.dictionary.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref>\n\n{|Class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:6em;\"| Country !!  Award !! Sponsor !!Notes\n|-\n| United States || [[Archon X Prize]] || [[X Prize Foundation]] || First team to rapidly, accurately and economically sequence 100 whole human genomes to an unprecedented level of accuracy<ref>{{cite web | title=The Archon Genomics XPRIZE presented by Express Scripts -- Overview | url=http://genomics.xprize.org/competition-details/prize-overview}}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Bateson Lecture]] || [[John Innes Centre]] || Genetics lecture<ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.jic.ac.uk/corporate/whats-on/named-lectures/bateson.htm| title= The Bateson Lecture| publisher= John Innes Centre| accessdate= 13 November 2010| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131109155313/http://www.jic.ac.uk/corporate/whats-on/named-lectures/bateson.htm| archive-date= 2013-11-09| url-status= dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Biffen Lecture]] || [[John Innes Centre]] || Genetics lecture<ref>{{citation |contribution=The Biffen Lecture |url=http://www.jic.ac.uk/corporate/whats-on/named-lectures/biffen.htm |publisher=John Inne