46}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last5=Poldrack|first5=Russell|last4=Poline|first4=Jean-Baptiste|last3=N. Kennedy|first3=David|last2=Nichols|first2=Thomas|last=Gorgolewski|first=Krzysztof|date=2017-11-03|title=Replication Award Creation Kit|url=https://figshare.com/articles/Replication_Award_Creation_Kit/5567083|language=en|doi=10.6084/m9.figshare.5567083.v1}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Perl-UNC Prize]] || [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] || Outstanding discoveries and seminal insights in neuroscience<ref>{{Citation | title = Member Obituaries: Edward R. Perl | journal =Society for Neuroscience | date = 2014 | url = http://www.sfn.org/Member-Center/Member-Obituaries/NS/Edward-R-Perl }}</ref><ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.med.unc.edu/neuroscience/perl-prize/|title=The Perl-UNC Neuroscience Prize |publisher=UNC Neuroscience Center|accessdate=7 February 2020}} </ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Potamkin Prize]] || Potamkin Foundation, [[American Academy of Neurology]] || Achievements in emerging areas of research in Pick's disease, Alzheimer's disease and other dementias<ref>{{cite web|url= http://tools.aan.com/science/awards/?fuseaction=home.info&id=13|title= Potamkin Prize for Research in Pick's, Alzheimer's, and Related Diseases|publisher= American Academy of Neurology|accessdate= 24 June 2015|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150907233726/http://tools.aan.com/science/awards/?fuseaction=home.info&id=13|archive-date= 7 September 2015|url-status= dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Ralph W. Gerard Prize in Neuroscience]] || [[Society for Neuroscience]] || Scientist who has made significant contributions to neuroscience throughout his or her career<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sfn.org/about/history-of-sfn/the-creation-of-neuroscience/~/media/SfN/Images/History%20of%20SfN/pdf/HistoryofSfN.ashx|title=The creation of Neuroscience|date=2018-10-06|website=Society for Neuroscience}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sfn.org/Careers/Awards/Li